{"word":"δεινότης","slug":"δεινότης","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>δεινότης</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:δεινός'><el>δεινός</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>terribleness</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>: <i>harshness, sternness, severity</i>, <el>νόμων</el> <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>natural ability, cleverness, shrewdness</i>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b>; <a href='S:especially'>esp.</a> in an orator, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}